        {
          "username": "les rosen",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "106400506257230405157",
          "user_review_count": 19,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDOTZP9hlFc67r1H0IDiTbZ8LphD-iCY1XsrItqqMSdlA7CjU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "This has to be the best hospital in the V.A. the doctors for the most part are part of NYU hospital, which is top hospital in the USA.\nVets. This is the place to trust your health too.\nI have just read many reviews most good some not so good. It is sad they do not have a reply as I would have liked to have answered the nasty one.\nI have been going to the VA for over 20 years and NYC VA is the best.\nYes there are times you msy have to wait because an illness is worse than patient reported.  Guys and girls keep in mind we are getting NYC NYU medical treatment as a thank you for our service. Yes there maybe some small co payment. Ask yourself wh a t would happen to you without the V.A. then one day drop by some of the other VA hospitals go as close as The Bronx or Brooklyn. Go to Long Island beautiful hospital even a golf course however you will not be treated like the NYC doctors or staff. Have to wait go tonthe second floor Cafe. The prices are cheap and relax and say thank you to the doctors and staff.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xNM1VuSndObkIzVmxZMWIzUjJTekJOWDAxd2JrRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x927f33ed58d181d6!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlM3UnJwNnB3VlY1b3R2SzBNX01wbkE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 months ago",
