          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIy4G9-ltXFkDwa9iALeMN4KK-YRxooRIHTKvBcvBcRm-4DeQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "The Urology clinic was amazing I appreciate their help fully. The mental health clinic, no help I went for help and was told everyone in a appointment but heres a number...im not even going to tell a doctor youre here so he could help you...what are you serious, I just left. The ER...what made me really give up, I get my pressure taken fine then nearly everyone is staring at me I guess the lady in front let everyone know that someone that needs mental help is here isnt that nice. Then the mental health nurse comes I could tell she didnt wanna be bothered with me what confirmed it is her ask if I want to \"Harm myself\" I say no\" she rolled her eyes im already feel uneasy. Then people are smiling and looking at me talking to other coworkers, one even laughed. I left, the nurse stops me and says \"Youre waiting because a few people were ahead of you\", then its \"No youre next\" seconds later. Youre a liar. I hate you people! I hope noone ever goes their for help because I cant imagine how many people took their own lives because of this place. Thank you to the Ladies in the Urology clinic for encouraging me to get help. This experience just broke me even more and honestly I dont want to step foot in another VA again ill just buy health care.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oNFJVVjZZbXcxY0VGb1NIUmpkV3hvVGxVelRFRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x927f33ed58d181d6!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnh4RUV6Ymw1cEFoSHRjdWxoTlUzTEE%7C%7C?hl=en",
